We first note that in these transactions only some of the “Sale” lines carry a tax‐component (a “tax_amount”). (The “Initial …” records just open the balance, and none of the “Purchase”, “Expense”, “Depreciation” or “Interest” transactions include any tax value.) In our “Sale” rows the tax collected is recorded in the “tax_amount” field. (A “taxes payable” balance is normally computed as tax collected from customers (on sales) less any tax credits/refunds from purchases – and if there is no credit then the “taxes payable” is simply the sum of tax amounts from sales; also the beginning (initial) balance of taxes payable is zero.)
